<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/weblab/footer.css"><meta charset="UTF-8"><meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"><title>Spot the Difference Game</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href=style.css">

      <div class="container">
        <div class="title">
          <h1>Spot The Difference!</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="container-bonus">
          <div class="headings">
            <h1>Thomas A. Edison CTE HS</h1>
            
            <h2>Final Project Ghost School</h2>
            
            <h2>Samantha payero</h2>
          </div>
          <div>
          <img class="imgofme" src="imgofme" alt="imgofme" width="35%;"
        
               </div> 
      <!-- Wave effect container for instructions or game levels -->

      <div class="container2">
        <div class="wave" id="easy-level">

          <h2>Instructions</h2>

          <p>Hover over this section to reveal more details about the game, that way you can follow the instructions carefully to play each level!</p>

          <p>In this game of, "Spot the Difference" there are 3 levels you can choose from depending on how difficult you'd like to play the game.</p>

          <p>These 3 levels are:</p>

          <div class="ol">
            <ol class="centered-list">
              <li id="easy">Easy</li>
              <li id="medium">Medium</li>
              <li id="hard">Hard</li>
            </ol>
          </div>

          <p>Throughout each level, you are able to see multiple objects, you have only a few seconds to look at each of them. After that, BOOM! Your screen turns black and turns back on shortly after.</p>
          <p>Only up to 3 out of all the objects have changed. As you progress through each level, spotting these differences will only get harder and harder. Can you spot the difference?</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wave2" id="easy-level">
          <h2>Easy Level</h2>
          <!-- Rollover image for the 'Easy' level -->

          <div class="level">

            <h3>Spot the Difference! Difficulty: <span style="color: lightgreen">Easy</span></h3>

            <img src="lvl1.png" alt="Easy Level Image" width="500" 
            
                 <p>You have 5 seconds to view the items in the room. Drag the cursor out of the room once the 5 seconds are up!</p>
          
          <div class="wave3" id="medium level">
            <h2>medium Level</h2>
            <!-- Rollover image for the 'Easy' level -->

            <div class="level">

              <h3>Spot the Difference! Difficulty: <span style="color: #ffb826">medium</span></h3>

              <img src="lvl2.png" alt="lvl2.png" width="500"

                   onmouseover="this.src='lvl2.png';"

                   onmouseout="this.src='lvl22.png';">
              
              <div class="wave4" id="Hard level">
                <h2>Hard Level</h2>
                <!-- Rollover image for the 'Easy' level -->

                <div class="level">

                  <h3>Spot the Difference! Difficulty: <span style="color: #ff0000">Hard</span></h3>

                  <img src="lvl3.png." alt="lvl3.png" width="500"

                       onmouseover="this.src='lvl3.png';"

                       onmouseout="this.src='lvl33.png';">


</body>
</html>


